	(616,348,'_seo_cached_filtered__content_new','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-898\" title=\"parents tools for kids testing\" alt=\"parents tools for kids testing\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/parents.png\" width=\"392\" height=\"348\" /></p>\n<p>[one_half]</p>\n<h2>[icon name=\"icon-bolt\"] <span style=\"color: #993300;\">E</span>ducational Games - Give Your Kids an Advantage ?</h2>\n<p>Young learners today are being consumed by the convergence of technology with education. <strong>Educational Games</strong> and technology are part of their world more then ever. As technology becomes more accessible through phones, mobile consoles, gaming devices, laptops and tablets, there is massive potential to give your student the upper hand advantage in comparison to other students. Give them the right tools and you can Improve Student Performance.</p>\n<p>A recent report on Elementary Educational Games andEducational Games for Teens was produced in March of 2013. This report was funded by the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation and carried out by SRI International. The research examined 77 studies that were conducted and focused on learning outcomes. The results of their finding showed games Improve Student Performance.</p> &nbsp;\n<h2>[icon name=\"icon-bar-chart\"] Improve Student Performance ?</h2>\n<p>Your students are in the most competitive time in history. The world has become flat. Content is produced all over the world and available instantly to anyone. Students have access to more information than when you grew up and also have more pressure to compete in this global environment. How do you give your student a better chance? Do you know how they compare against the rest of the world? Do you even know how they compare against kids in their classroom today? Class Compete gives your students the opportunity to use technology, creative new testing styles and compete against others in their classroom and the world. Our goal is to increase student performance, and for the first time you will instantly know results and most importantly how they compare. Giving your student a competitive edge is a download away. Try our Free Online Educational Games!</p>\n<p>[/one_half][one_half_last]</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">[button icon=\" icon-user\" size=\"large\" type=\"primary\" value=\" &gt; Join ClassCompete Now! \" title=\"Join/Login ClassCompete\" href=\"http://www.classcompete.com/#parent-login\"]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote><p>[icon name=\"icon-quote-left\"] When digital games were compared to other instruction conditions without digital games there was a moderate to strong effect in favor of digital games in terms of broad cognitive competencies... This is equivalent to a 62% success rate in the digital game groups relative to a 50% success rate in the other instruction conditions...</p>\n<p><strong>This means that the students...in the control group (no game) could have been raised 12% in cognitive learning outcomes if they had received the digital game.</strong> [icon name=\"icon-quote-right\"][/one_half_last]</p></blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2></h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">[row class=\"row-fluid\"]</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">[col class=\"span3\"]Problem Solving Skills [icon name=\"icon-group\"][/col]</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">[col class=\"span3\"]<span style=\"color: #993300;\">Encourage Creativity</span> [icon name=\"icon-globe\"][/col]</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">[col class=\"span3\"]Test Prep- Made Easy [icon name=\"icon-check\"][/col]</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">[col class=\"span3\"]<span style=\"color: #993300;\">Happy Kids!</span> <img style=\"border: 0px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-tinymce/addons/emotions/img/popobig/haha.png\" width=\"36\" height=\"36\" border=\"0\" />[/col]<br class=\"nc\" />[/row]</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[button icon=\" icon-user\" size=\"large\" type=\"primary\" value=\" &gt; Join ClassCompete Now! \" title=\"Join/Login ClassCompete\" href=\"http://www.classcompete.com/#parent-login\"]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n'),
