	(2548,813,'_seo_cached_filtered__content_new','<p>[one_half]</p>\n<p><strong>1. Operations and Algebraic Thinking</strong></p>\n<p>a. Real World Problems- 1.OA.1</p>\n<p>b. Addition &amp; Subtraction Properties- 1.OA.3, 1.OA.4</p>\n<p>c. Addition and Subtraction Facts 1.OA.5, 1.OA.6</p>\n<p>d. Number Sentences-1.OA.7</p>\n<p><strong>2. Numbers &amp; Operations in Ten Base</strong></p>\n<p>a. Counting Numbers-1.NBT.1</p>\n<p>b. Reading and Writing Numbers-1.NBT.1</p>\n<p>c. Place Value- 1.NBT.1</p>\n<p>d. Compare &amp; Order Numbers- 1.NBT.3</p>\n<p>e. Addition &amp; Subtraction Strategies- 1.NBT.4</p>\n<p><strong>3. Measurement &amp; Data</strong></p>\n<p>a. Length- 1.MD.1, 1.MD.2</p>\n<p>b. Time- 1.MD.3</p>\n<p>c. Represent &amp; Interpret Data- M.D.4</p>\n<p><strong>4. Geometry</strong></p>\n<p>a. Shapes- 1.G.1, 1.G.2, 1.G.3</p>\n<p>[/one_half]</p>\n<p>[one_half_last]</p>\n<h1>[icon name=\"icon-bullhorn\"]</h1>\n<p><strong>Class Compete</strong> has strategically organized the Common Core in sections we find most useful for student learning and optimizing testing results. We suggest having students use challenges in the appropriate sequence and engage for a minimum of 5 minutes in a challenge.</p>\n<p>Encourage students to work together or alone to find answers to difficult questions them to think come back and compete again for maximum results.</p>\n<p>[/one_half_last]</p>\n'),
