	(748,1,'2013-12-20 14:42:24','2013-12-20 18:42:24','<h2><span style=\"color: #993300;\">W</span>ho is Class Compete?</h2>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">We are an experienced group of professionals that have been involved in education for over 20 years. In this time we believe the educational process can be broken into 4 distinct pieces:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">[icon name=\"icon-chevron-right\"]Gather Data</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">[icon name=\"icon-chevron-right\"]Teaching</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">[icon name=\"icon-chevron-right\"]<strong>Testing</strong></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">[icon name=\"icon-chevron-right\"]Application of Knowledge</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">In the last few years we have focused a large portion of that time with after school tutoring.....watching....and listening......</p>\n&nbsp;\n<h2>[icon name=\"icon-medkit\"]<span style=\"color: #993300;\">W</span>hat will Class Compete Fix?</h2>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Our analysis showed that the \"Teaching\" aspect has evolved and continues to evolve at a rapid rate with E-Learning, Videos and Learning Management Systems. Currently there is an entire new paradigm in education called: The Common Core Standards. This will be the first time there is a common set of educational standards across the US. Its a rigorous new curriculum and projected to fully begin in the 2014-2015 school year.</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">As new educational paradigms keep evolving, the Testing piece, however, has not. We aim to make the testing and reinforcement process more dynamic and fun, and also prepare students better for the new tests associated to new learning paradigms. Currently students test with items like bubble sheets? Really? Still? Parents waiting for quarterly report cards to find out how their child is doing? That\'s the best information that can be provided? We didn\'t think so....</p>\n&nbsp;\n<h2>[icon name=\"icon-road\"] <span style=\"color: #993300;\">H</span>ow Class Compete Works !</h2>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Mobile technology has changed the face of education and Class Compete aims to change the face of Testing.</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Class Compete will:</strong></span>\n<strong>1. Focus on what students AND teachers are ultimately judged on: TESTING</strong>\n<strong> 2. Combine current student interests- mobile &amp; 3-D gaming with testing</strong>\n<strong> 3. Attract all 3 student learning types- Auditory, Tactile, Visual</strong>\n<strong>4. Offer a marketplace for teachers to share their assessment styles</strong></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Class Compete is: Gamification of Assessments using a 3-d experience students are used to, on a mobile-first strategy. Children will play \"challenges\" ( topic based assessments) that teachers assign, competing against their classmates in a 3-d game. The Teachers AND Parents will then get real-time performance results locally as well nationally.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #993300;\">We aim to merge interactive gaming, testing, competition with mobile technologies. Step up and take a challenge We ARE.. Class Compete!</span></strong></p>','Who Is Class Compete?','','inherit','closed','closed','','708-autosave-v1','','','2013-12-20 14:42:24','2013-12-20 18:42:24','',708,'http://www.classcompete.com/748',0,'revision','',0),
