	(761,1,'2013-10-06 12:31:20','2013-10-06 16:31:20','[row class=\"row-fluid\"]<br class=\"nc\" />[col class=\"span6\"]\r\n<h3>What We Do  [icon name=\"icon-lightbulb\"]</h3>\r\nRecent studies show kids have the highest engagement with casual gaming on hand held devices. With this knowledge, and a little bit of magic and luck, we combined education testing and gaming. Our gaming environment is focused entirely around assessments. There are many different learning tools available, but how does one know if those tools are working? Should you be using a different tool for your student? Class Compete aims to offer real time information via an academic assessment of a skill. Teachers and Parents alike can know how their students compare against others and make timely decisions on their academic progress.\r\n\r\n[/col]<br class=\"nc\" />[col class=\"span6\"]\r\n<h3>Data... Data... Data...  [icon name=\"icon-bar-chart\"]</h3>\r\nWe studied 100,000 children from 2010-2013 where supplemental educational services were provided to students 2\'nd to 8\'th grades using 3 styles of math tutoring. Improvements were measured via pre and post tutoring tests with average point gains shown below.* The results are clear: students are relating to cool new technology more than ever before.\r\n\r\n[progress value=88 text=\'Teacher PLUS Technology:     <em>8.68 pts</em>\'][progress value=70 text=\'Online Teacher:             <em>7.23 pts</em>\'][progress value=55 text=\'Teacher:   <em>5.62 pts</em>\']\r\n\r\n<i>*Data provided by Learn It Systems</i>\r\n\r\n[/col]<br class=\"nc\" />[/row]\r\n\r\n[team]','The Idea','','inherit','closed','closed','','83-revision-v1','','','2013-10-06 12:31:20','2013-10-06 16:31:20','',83,'http://www.classcompete.com/83-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
