	(812,1,'2013-11-25 13:23:52','2013-11-25 17:23:52','<h2>[icon name=\"icon-book\"]<span style=\"color: #993300;\">W</span>ho is Class Compete?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">We are an experienced group of professionals that have been involved in education for over 20 years. In this time we believe the educational process can be broken into 4 distinct pieces:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">[icon name=\"icon-chevron-right\"]Gather Data</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">[icon name=\"icon-chevron-right\"]Teaching</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">[icon name=\"icon-chevron-right\"]<strong>Testing</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">[icon name=\"icon-chevron-right\"]Application</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">In the last few years we have focused a large portion of that time with after school tutoring.....watching....and listening......</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>[icon name=\"icon-medkit\"]<span style=\"color: #993300;\">W</span>hat will Class Compete Fix?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Our analysis showed that the \"Teaching\" aspect has evolved and continues to evolve at a rapid rate with E-Learning, Videos and Learning Management Systems etc. The \"<strong>Testing</strong>\" piece, however, has evolved the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">least</span> over the years. Bubble Sheets? Really? Still? Parents waiting for quarterly report cards to find out how their child is doing? That\'s the best information that can be provided? We didn\'t think so....</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>[icon name=\"icon-road\"] <span style=\"color: #993300;\">H</span>ow Class Compete Works !</h2>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Mobile technology has changed the paradigm of education and Class Compete aims to change the \"Testing\" paradigm.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Class Compete will:</strong></span>\r\n<strong>1. Focus on what students AND teachers are ultimately judged on: THE TEST</strong>\r\n<strong> 2. Anticipate the increased penetration of tablets and respond</strong>\r\n<strong> 3. Attract all 3 student learning \"types\" to the platform</strong>\r\n<strong>4. Create a marketplace for teachers to share their assessment styles</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Class Compete is: Gamification of Assessments using a 3-d experience students are use to, on a mobile-first strategy. Children will play \"challenges\" ( topic based assessments) that teachers assign, competing against their classmates in a 3-d game. The Teachers AND Parents will then get real-time performance results locally as well nationally.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #993300;\">We aim to merge interactive gaming, testing, competition with mobile technologies. Step up and take a challenge We ARE.. Class Compete!</span></strong></p>','Who Is Class Compete?','','inherit','closed','closed','','708-revision-v1','','','2013-11-25 13:23:52','2013-11-25 17:23:52','',708,'http://www.classcompete.com/708-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(813,1,'2013-11-26 15:48:59','2013-11-26 19:48:59','[one_half]\r\n\r\n<strong>1. Operations and Algebraic Thinking</strong>\r\n\r\na. Real World Problems- 1.OA.1\r\n\r\nb. Addition &amp; Subtraction Properties- 1.OA.3, 1.OA.4\r\n\r\nc. Addition and Subtraction Facts 1.OA.5, 1.OA.6\r\n\r\nd. Number Sentences-1.OA.7\r\n\r\n<strong>2. Numbers &amp; Operations in Ten Base</strong>\r\n\r\na. Counting Numbers-1.NBT.1\r\n\r\nb. Reading and Writing Numbers-1.NBT.1\r\n\r\nc. Place Value- 1.NBT.1\r\n\r\nd. Compare &amp; Order Numbers- 1.NBT.3\r\n\r\ne. Addition &amp; Subtraction Strategies- 1.NBT.4\r\n\r\n<strong>3. Measurement &amp; Data</strong>\r\n\r\na. Length- 1.MD.1, 1.MD.2\r\n\r\nb. Time- 1.MD.3\r\n\r\nc. Represent &amp; Interpret Data- M.D.4\r\n\r\n<strong>4. Geometry</strong>\r\n\r\na. Shapes- 1.G.1, 1.G.2, 1.G.3\r\n\r\n[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<h1>[icon name=\"icon-bullhorn\"]</h1>\r\n<strong>Class Compete</strong> has strategically organized the Common Core in sections we find most useful for student learning and optimizing testing results. We suggest having students use challenges in the appropriate sequence and engage for a minimum of 5 minutes in a challenge.\r\n\r\nEncourage students to work together or alone to find answers to difficult questions then come back and compete again for maximum results.\r\n\r\n[/one_half_last]','Math 1\'st Grade','','publish','closed','closed','','math-1st-grade','','','2013-12-27 01:15:07','2013-12-27 05:15:07','',0,'http://www.classcompete.com/?post_type=portfolio&#038;p=813',0,'portfolio','',0),
