	(946,1,'2014-01-04 13:18:30','2014-01-04 17:18:30','[two_third]<img class=\"wp-image-896 alignleft\" title=\"teacher tools\" alt=\"teacher tools\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/teacher.png\" width=\"402\" height=\"328\" />[/two_third][one_third_last][button icon=\" icon-user\" size=\"large\" type=\"primary\" value=\" &gt; Join ClassCompete Now! \" title=\"Join/Login ClassCompete\" href=\"http://teacher.classcompete.com\"][/one_third_last]\r\n\r\n[one_half]\r\n<h2>[icon name=\"icon-pencil\"] <span style=\"color: #993300;\">E</span>ngaging Studentsis Hard</h2>\r\n<strong>Teaching Challenges</strong> in the classroom abound like never seen before. Distractions for students are everywhere and keeping them focused is difficult. We at Class Compete understand your problems! How can you compete with the influx of technology in our everyday lives. From billboards, to mobile phones, students are becoming more technology savvy but also their attention is quickly diminishing. Jane McGonigal, an educational gaming guru, recently spoke at the 2013 ISTE conference and demonstrated how engagement is going down in the classroom.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>[icon name=\"icon-magic\"]Games as a Teaching Strategy</h2>\r\nIt is well documented that each student learns differently, thereby creating massive classroom challenges.Teachers spend a tremendous amount of time creating lesson plans that are creative and teaching through activities. With all this effort, however, how can one check if they understand what you are teaching? At the ISTE Conference Jane McGonigal gave evidence of students playing extensive amounts of electronic games.\r\n\r\nClass Compete offers a Classroom Testing Measurement and Evaluation system. Itgives you a Classroom Testing and Evaluation platform to get instant results, allows using games for learning. By using 3-D games, it appeals to ALL learning types!!! Students engage using a 3-D gaming environment playing any teaching challenge you assign to them. It will work on Tablets as well as Desktops and Laptops.\r\n\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote>[icon name=\"icon-quote-left\"]...the level of engagement students report with their education drops as they continue through the system...76 percent of elementary school students report feeling engaged in the classroom, that number drops to 61 percent for middle schoolers, and only 44 percent...for high schooler\'s [icon name=\"icon-quote-right\"]\r\n\r\n[icon name=\"icon-quote-left\"]...games are a space of maximum engagement...nearly all children (99 percent of boys under 18 and 94 percent of girls) are playing games regularly (for at least an hour per day)... schools and teachers will have to compete with and harness the sense of maximum engagement that students feel while playing those games... [icon name=\"icon-quote-right\"]</blockquote>\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n<h2>[icon name=\"icon-trophy\"]  <span style=\"color: #993300;\">H</span>ow Does <span style=\"color: #993300;\">Class Compete</span> Work?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[row class=\"row-fluid\"]<br class=\"nc\" />[col class=\"span4\"][button icon=\"icon-wrench\" size=\"large\" type=\"success\" value=\" Step 1 &gt;  Setup Classroom\"][/col]<br class=\"nc\" />[col class=\"span4\"][button icon=\"icon-fire\" size=\"large\" type=\"default\" value=\" Step 2 &gt;  Assign Challenges\"][/col]<br class=\"nc\" />[col class=\"span4\"][button icon=\"icon-bar-chart\" size=\"large\" type=\"info\" value=\" Step 3 &gt;  See Results\"][/col]<br class=\"nc\" />[/row]</p>\r\nNo longer do you have to wait to grade quizzes, or wait to see how your students perform on standardized tests. It is an instant <strong>classroom testing</strong> system that allows you to measure performance of the lessons you just taught. Teacher performance is now being judged on classroom testing results; arm yourself with what works to give you instant feedback. You will see how students compare not only against each other but with different classrooms from the district, the County, State and Country!!! With the Common Core Standards changing classroom testing procedures, it is important now - more than ever to have the best Classroom Testing and Measurement system possible.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[button icon=\" icon-user\" size=\"large\" type=\"primary\" value=\" &gt; Join ClassCompete Now! \" title=\"Join/Login ClassCompete\" href=\"http://teacher.classcompete.com\"]</p>\r\n&nbsp;','Teacher Information','','inherit','closed','closed','','341-revision-v1','','','2014-01-04 13:18:30','2014-01-04 17:18:30','',341,'http://www.classcompete.com/341-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
